      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Minimum wage hikes, especially those driven by urban interests, can be detrimental to small businesses in midwestern towns. These regions often have a lower cost of living, and a higher minimum wage can increase operational costs without a corresponding rise in local spending power. This can lead to reduced hiring, higher prices, or even business closures, ultimately harming the local economy and job market. It's essential to consider the unique economic conditions of each area before implementing such policies.",
