      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument that higher minimum wages boost local spending is a common one, but it's not always as effective as it sounds. In many small towns, the increased wages might not translate into higher local spending because residents may have less disposable income due to the higher costs of living. This can lead to reduced consumer spending, which can hurt local businesses. Additionally, higher wages can lead to increased prices as businesses try to offset their costs, which can further reduce consumer spending. So, while the intention is good, the reality can be quite different, and the impact on small businesses can be negative.",
